---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Best for US Expats', href: '/best/us-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Mexico Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
  { title: 'Spain Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Network Size', cigna: '1.5M+ global', aetna: '1.7M+ (incl. US Aetna)' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', cigna: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', cigna: 'Gold/Platinum', aetna: 'Prime/Platinum' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', cigna: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'Maternity', cigna: 'Optional (10-mo wait)', aetna: 'Optional (12-mo wait)' },
  { feature: 'Dental', cigna: 'Optional', aetna: 'Optional module' },
  { feature: 'Vision', cigna: 'Optional', aetna: 'Optional module' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', cigna: 'Included', aetna: 'Up to $1M' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', cigna: 'Add-on (40-60% more)', aetna: 'Integrated' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Gold (ex-US)' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna Prime (ex-US)' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Age 30', cigna: '$140-200/mo', aetna: '$170-240/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 45', cigna: '$220-300/mo', aetna: '$250-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Age 55', cigna: '$350-450/mo', aetna: '$380-500/mo' },
  { profile: 'With US coverage', cigna: '+40-60%', aetna: 'Included' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global vs Aetna International"
  description="Compare Cigna Global and Aetna International side by side. Coverage, pricing, and which is better for expats with or without US healthcare needs."
  headline="Cigna Global vs Aetna International: Full Comparison"
  subheadline="Two healthcare giants in the international market. The key question: do you need US coverage?"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global and Aetna International are both major players in international health insurance, backed by large US healthcare corporations. But they serve different markets best: Cigna excels globally while Aetna shines for US expats.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Part of The Cigna Group</li>
        <li>1.5M+ providers worldwide</li>
        <li>Silver, Gold, Platinum tiers</li>
        <li>Strong customer service reputation</li>
        <li>Excellent for families</li>
        <li>US coverage as add-on (costly)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Aetna International</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Part of CVS Health / Aetna</li>
        <li>1.7M+ providers (incl. full US network)</li>
        <li>Pioneer (tiered) and Navigator (modular)</li>
        <li>Integrated US coverage</li>
        <li>Best for US expats</li>
        <li>Strong corporate/employer options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Critical Difference: US Coverage</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      <strong>Aetna International includes US coverage by design.</strong> Their plans seamlessly integrate with Aetna's domestic US network. <strong>Cigna Global treats US coverage as an expensive add-on</strong>—adding 40-60% to premiums. If you need US healthcare access, this difference alone may determine your choice.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from Cigna Global and Aetna International."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both providers offer comprehensive coverage. The main differences are in US integration and plan structure.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Aetna's US network integration is seamless—no add-on pricing, direct billing at US hospitals</li>
    <li>Cigna has a marginally larger global (non-US) network reputation</li>
    <li>Aetna's Navigator plans offer modular customization; Cigna uses fixed tiers</li>
    <li>Cigna has a slight edge in family and maternity-focused features</li>
    <li>Both have 24/7 multilingual support and mobile apps</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Plan Structure</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> uses simple tiers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Silver:</strong> Inpatient and day patient care</li>
    <li><strong>Gold:</strong> Silver plus outpatient</li>
    <li><strong>Platinum:</strong> Gold plus enhanced benefits</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> offers two product lines:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pioneer:</strong> Tiered plans similar to Cigna</li>
    <li><strong>Navigator:</strong> Modular plans—choose core hospital coverage plus optional outpatient, dental, vision, maternity modules</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Aetna's Navigator flexibility can save money if you don't need every benefit included in Cigna's tiers.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Pricing is comparable when excluding US coverage. The gap widens significantly when US access is needed.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Without US coverage, Cigna is often slightly cheaper</li>
    <li>With US coverage, Aetna becomes more competitive (integrated vs add-on)</li>
    <li>Both offer deductible options from $0 to $5,000+</li>
    <li>Higher deductibles reduce premiums 20-35%</li>
    <li>Aetna Navigator may be cheaper if you only need specific modules</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">US Coverage Cost Example</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      A 40-year-old on Cigna Gold excluding US: ~$260/month. Adding US coverage: ~$390-415/month (+50%). That same person on Aetna Prime with US coverage included: ~$280-380/month. <strong>For US expats, Aetna can be significantly cheaper.</strong>
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="Compare actual quotes for your age and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> has 1.5 million+ providers worldwide with strong direct-billing relationships. Their network is particularly well-developed in Europe, Asia, and the Middle East. US providers are available but at premium pricing.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> includes 1.7 million+ providers globally, with the key advantage being seamless Aetna US network access. You can use the same network domestically that millions of Americans use.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna:</strong> Online portal and mobile app. Claims typically processed in 5-10 business days. Known for user-friendly interface and good customer service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna:</strong> Online portal, mobile app, and email submission. Claims typically processed in 5-10 days. Direct billing available at network providers globally.
  </p>
  <p>
    Both have comparable claims experiences. Cigna's portal is slightly more polished; Aetna's US integration is smoother.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna</strong> is consistently rated highly for customer service. 24/7 support in multiple languages with a reputation for helpful, knowledgeable representatives.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna</strong> also offers 24/7 multilingual support. They provide dedicated case managers for complex situations, which is valuable for serious medical needs.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You don't need US coverage</li>
        <li>You're living in Europe, Asia, or Middle East</li>
        <li>Customer service quality is your top priority</li>
        <li>You have a family and value maternity options</li>
        <li>You prefer simple tiered plans</li>
        <li>You want the most recognized global brand</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Aetna International If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You need US healthcare access</li>
        <li>You're a US citizen or expat</li>
        <li>You visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>You may repatriate to the US eventually</li>
        <li>You want modular, customizable coverage</li>
        <li>You work for a US company abroad</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    The choice between Cigna Global and Aetna International largely comes down to one question: <strong>do you need US coverage?</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>If you don't need US coverage</strong>, Cigna Global is often the better choice. Their customer service reputation is excellent, pricing is competitive, and their global network is well-established. Families particularly appreciate Cigna's options.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>If you need US coverage</strong>, Aetna International is the clear winner. Their integrated US network and competitive pricing (without the 40-60% add-on premium) make them the smart choice for Americans abroad. The Navigator modular plans also offer flexibility that Cigna doesn't match.
  </p>
  <p>
    Both are excellent insurers with strong financial backing. You won't go wrong with either—but matching the right one to your needs (especially around US coverage) will save you money and headaches.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
